Governor of the Central Bank of Nigerians (CBN), Godwin Emefiele has stated that he is focused on fighting inflation and designing a robust monetary policy for the country. He said this in a series of posts made via his official Twitter handle on Monday. The CBN governor was reacting to reports regarding his rumoured bid for presidency in 2023. Also Read: 2023: If Tinubu, Rochas Ticket Emanates, I’ll Win –Okorocha “My focus at this time is a robust monetary policy and fighting inflation which is now a global problem; building a strong financial system in an increasingly uncertain global economy,” the tweet reads. “Development finance and supporting farmers & manufacturers in our self-sufficiency and import substitution drive; raising N15 trillion for InfraCo infrastructure financing; “Building a world-class International Financial Center in Lagos; as we support the @MBuhari Administration to finish strong.#NoDistractionsPlease.”